CMD/ENTRYPOINT : execute the commands post container created.
CMD : over write
CMD ["yum", "install", "git", "-y"]
docker run <image_name>
ENTRYPOINT : append the values
ENTRYPOINT ["yum", "install", "git", "-y"]
docker run <image_name> maven    here install git as well as maven also 
Simple understanding:
CMD → gets overridden if you pass arguments in docker run
ENTRYPOINT → does not override, it appends arguments
ARG - used to pause the variable creating images (we can't access inside the container)
ENV - used to oause the vaiables we can access inside the container
we can change ARG vlues in runtime but not ENV values 


